TIPOOL output files are available in Dataset 1.  RNA and RNA Immunoprecipitation (RIP) sequencing data are available from the GEO database under accession number GSE132425, and processed data are also available in Dataset 2.   Raw proteomic data are available in the PRIDE database (Project accession # PXD013847);  processed data are available in Dataset 2, and normalized protein abundance data are available in Dataset 3.</p><p>The following datasets were generated:</p><p><element-citation id="dataset1" publication-type="data" specific-use="isSupplementedBy"><person-group person-group-type="author"><collab>Hose</collab></person-group><year iso-8601-date="2019">2019</year><source>DNA mapping data</source><ext-link ext-link-type="uri" xlink:href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/bioproject/?term=PRJNA548343">http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/bioproject/?term=PRJNA548343</ext-link><comment>SRA, PRJNA548343</comment></element-citation></p></sec><supplementary-material><ext-link xlink:href="elife-52063-supp-v1.zip">Download zip</ext-link><p>Any figures and tables for this article are included in the PDF. The zip folder contains additional supplemental files.</p></supplementary-material></sec></back></article>